{"build_type":"executable","module_name":"verify-kernel-allocates-inside-handed-arena","package_name":"verify-kernel-allocates-inside-handed-arena","description":"Phase B proof kernel. Invoked by the boot launcher after the loader has handed it a memory arena by seeding the allocator globals. Reads the arena cursor and end, allocates a probe block through allocate_bytes_from_mmap_arena, then emits a falsifiable report: headroom before allocation (a multi-megabyte headroom proves it is the handed arena rather than a default one-megabyte chunk), whether the allocation address lands inside the handed arena, whether the arena end stayed unchanged (no new host chunk grabbed), and how far the cursor advanced. Pure observation plus one allocation; no host syscalls of its own.","function_definitions":{"verify-kernel-allocates-inside-handed-arena":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"unused_first","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"unused_second","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"thousand","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1000},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"probe","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4096},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"neg1","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"alu_operation","operator":"-","target":"neg1","lhs":{"value":"zero"},"rhs":{"value":"one"}},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"cur0","name":"arena_cursor_address"},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"end0","name":"are